message: Just felt like helping out a fellow victim of Kellymoat :)
Unsourced, which is hugely hypocritical for you to do.
/* Clerk, CheckUser, and/or patrolling admin comments */ Sorry

Yes, because it was unsourced as well. All of this is unsourced, and it's funny that you're defending this, as you asked someone else on your own talk page if they sourced something. Pretty contradictory.
Why would they do that? I'd be reporting YOU.

Why are you reverting this? This is a constructive edit; it redirects the reader to the correct version of the song. You have no reason to revert this other than you personal feelings towards me and the anonymous user.
You are now engaged in an edit war, and their discography doesn't say that.
/* Edit warring on I See You */ new section
This edit makes it so that the reader is taken to her version of the song. Not sure why you're reverting that. Do you have a problem with this user?
See other pages. You clearly are not here to edit Wikipedia constructively.
You must source information. You are edit-warring.
More unsourced information. Do I need to report you?
Please provide a source, or else you are edit-warring.
/* Critical reception */ Not sure why MC score isn't displayed, and the scores reflect an overall mixed reception.
/* Track listing */ Not spelled that way on her website.
If Feeling Myself is a single, then it came before this. I will create a section for this on the talk page as well, but I don't see what the issue is here.
Kellymoat, it is listed as a single on The Pinkprint, so can we leave it like this please? I'm not trying to argue, and I brought this up on the talk page.
